{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/15/comments/32005684.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/15#comment-32005684"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/15.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 15, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Hokuyo link not spinning in Rviz"}, "content": {"raw": "The output for rostopic echo -c /multisense/lidar_scan has all ranges at -INF and intensities at 1.0. The header information is constant from scan to scan.\n\nIn Gazebo the lidar is moving.\n\n```\n#!c++\n\n\nUbuntu version: 14.04.5 LTS\nGazebo version: 7.4.0\nROS version: Indigo\n```\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The output for rostopic echo -c /multisense/lidar_scan has all ranges at -INF and intensities at 1.0. The header information is constant from scan to scan.</p>\n<p>In Gazebo the lidar is moving.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">Ubuntu</span> <span class=\"nl\">version</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mf\">14.04.5</span> <span class=\"n\">LTS</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Gazebo</span> <span class=\"nl\">version</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mf\">7.4.0</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ROS</span> <span class=\"nl\">version</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Indigo</span>\n</pre></div>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-11-08T23:38:05.902013+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Rud Merriam", "uuid": "{79efa10c-b8b6-4b55-9d05-7d0057e235cb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B79efa10c-b8b6-4b55-9d05-7d0057e235cb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B79efa10